<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xml:id="tbxLoad" xml:lang="en">
    <refnamediv>
        <refname>tbxLoad</refname>
        <refpurpose>load / unload a toolbox in the current session</refpurpose>
    </refnamediv>
    <refsynopsisdiv>
        <title>Syntax</title>
        <synopsis>
tbxLoad(name)
tbxUnload(name)
        </synopsis>
    </refsynopsisdiv>
    <refsection>
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>Run the toolbox native <literal>loader.sce</literal> / <literal>unloader.sce</literal>. Note that toolbox <emphasis>macros</emphasis> only become global when loaded at base scope; from a function or callback only the native gateways take effect immediately, so prefer enabling toolboxes through <link linkend="tbxManager">tbxManager</link> and relaunching.</para>
    </refsection>
    <refsection>
        <title>Examples</title>
        <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
tbxLoad("cgal");
]]></programlisting>
    </refsection>
